cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper proposes a method for improving sample efficiency in robotic grasping tasks using a combination of model-based and model-free deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The approach also incorporates imagination, which is a recent development in deep reinforcement learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The task involves vision-based grasping, which suggests the use of computer vision techniques and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the approach involves learning an ensemble of local dynamics models, which suggests the use of system identification techniques and falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
